ements are awarded throughout the year by various University units and organizations Employee Recognition Month Each November is Employee Recognition Month at UIC  This special time of year includes departmental ceremonies as well as campus wide programs  planned for the purpose of honoring faculty and staff  In addition to campus wide and individual department merit awards earned for outstanding achievements  UIC honors its employees for years of service beginning at five years and continuing after each five year increment  In       UIC honored over       employees for years of service   Employee Recognition Award Ceremony The Employee Recognition Award Ceremony  held each year at the Isadore and Sadie Dorin Forum at UIC  formerly known as the UIC Forum  is the official start of Employee Recognition Month  This campus wide program serves to publicly recognize work and community accomplishments which in turn help to build morale and motivate our employees   Employees with    or more years of service are honored  along with campus wide merit awards  At the conclusion of the ceremony  a reception will take place for all to visit and congratulate the recipients being honored  All members of the UIC community are welcome to attend      Event Information The      Employee Recognition Award Ceremony and Reception will be held on Tuesday  November         at the Isadore and Sadie Dorin Forum at UIC  Those awards to be recognized include the Award of Merit  CAPE Award  Janice Watkins Award  Physician of the Year  and Resident of the Year  Service Year Recognition honorees will include those celebrating                 and    years of eligible service to the university See the links below for the names of those recipients of Service Year Recognition Awards    through    years of service  the UIC Award of Merit  CAPE Award  Janice Watkins Award    Physician of the Year  and Resident of the Year  n n      Employee Recognition Recipients n n     Service Year Recognition Recipients   through    Years  n      Employee Recognition Recipients      Service Year Recognition Recipients   through    Years  The Employee Recognition Award Ceremony will recognize Award of Merit recipients  CAPE recipients  Janice Watkins Award recipients  and UIC service honorees with    years or more in five year increments  Additional campus awards recognized are the UI Health honors of Employee of the Year  Physician of the Year  and Resident of the Year Service Recognition Awards Service Recognition Awards recognize  Academic Professionals and Civil Service employees and faculty for years of service to UIC in five year increments starting with    years of service  Departmentally  employees are recognized for every   years of service UIC Service Year Policy     UIC Service Year Policy     Award of Merit The Award of Merit recognizes outstanding Academic Professionals and Civil Service employees  It is a university wide honor available to UIC campus staff who exhibit service  commitment  and dedication  Award recipients receive        and a memento gift  The included links will outline the nomination instructions  process and past recipients Please check back in April      for the Award of Merit nomination form and instructions as the      Employee Recognition nomination season is opened Award of Merit Past Recipients  PDF Award of Merit Past Recipients  PDF CAPE Award CAPE Award  was established in       It recognizes the demonstrated excellence of Academic Professional staff  The CAPE award is based on peer review broadly selected from the ranks of the Academic Professionals throughout campus  The CAPE Selection Committee is a standing committee of APAC and is chaired by an APAC member  The Selection Committee is made up of Academic Professionals from both the east and west campuses which may include past CAPE recipients  UIC faculty  Academic Professionals  Civil Service employees  and students can nominate a deserving Academic Professional for the award  In      there were six recipients of the CAPE Award  Honorees receive memento gift  a     and a        one time cash award      CAPE Website      CAPE Website Janice Watkins Award  The Janice Watkins Award recognizes exceptional Civil Service employees for their distinguished service to the University  Sponsored by the Staff Advisory Council  the design for the award is based on three interlocking components signifying the unity of faculty  staff  and students of the University of Illinois at Chicago  The award is a token of gratitude from the university and is awarded to Civil Service employees who exhibit a pleasant  warm demeanor and provide willing assistance to others and perform duties with diligence and dedication  The nominations can be submitted by faculty  staff  nJanice Watkins Award Website n Janice Watkins Award Website UI Health  Class Act Award  Employee of the Year  Physician of the Year Resident of the Year Hospital guests and staff may nominate UI Health employees for the Class Act Award and the Physician of the Year and Resident of the Year  These recipients continuously contribute to the delivery of world class patient care  regularly show good judgment and initiative  go above and beyond performance expectations  is a role model  demonstrates a willingness to become more efficient and effective when providing patient care  and exemplify the UI CARE behaviors  n UI Health Employee Recognition Webpage UI Health Employee Recognition Webpage Office of Faculty Affairs Faculty Awards Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research Researcher of the Year Award Researcher of the Year Award The Office of the Vice Chancellor for Student Affairs VCSA Contact  Dr  W  Clarke Douglas  Associate Vice Chancellor for Student Affairs  wcd uic edu wcd uic edu Vice Chancellor for Student Affairs Outstanding New Staff Award    nVice Chancellor for Student Affairs Outstanding Staff Award nVice Chancellor for Student Affairs Outstanding Program Award nVice Chancellor for Studen